00:21:32,074 --> 00:21:32,574
Very good.

223
00:21:33,496 --> 00:21:44,791
So, yes, and the final thing to say is that when we practice this on something so

224
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:49,286
so obvious as eating, which we have to do every day.

225
00:21:49,306 --> 00:21:50,468
It's not as though you can give up eating.

226
00:21:51,910 --> 00:21:55,434
So it's a constant little practice for us, a constant reminder.

227
00:21:56,696 --> 00:22:14,644
When we do that, we begin to realise that actually this cuts across everything in our lives, you know, in terms of our enjoyment of art, TV, you know, film and all that sort of stuff, our enjoyment of nature, the hobbies we have,

228
00:22:15,890 --> 00:22:21,898
Anything you enjoy, anything you enjoy will have that overlay of wanting something more from it.

229
00:22:22,819 --> 00:22:31,353
And of course, relationship, relationship with its obsessive, obsessive relationship, the obsessive part.

230
00:22:32,394 --> 00:22:45,053
And that's often manifests in the way that we try to manipulate the other, demand of the other, try to control the other, disappointed in the other, frustrated by the other.

231
00:22:45,286 --> 00:22:46,748
and so on and so forth.

232
00:22:46,768 --> 00:23:01,704
So this practice on just having a cup of tea with a biscuit will eventually bring that sort of insight into our lives and begin to change it.

233
00:23:02,445 --> 00:23:06,470
And going back to what we said about the Eightfold Path, this is the feedback.

234
00:23:06,549 --> 00:23:14,179
This is the feedback from our right understanding through right action.

235
00:23:14,564 --> 00:23:19,256
And that reinforces the insight, right?

236
00:23:19,276 --> 00:23:21,923
It makes the insight more and more real for us.

237
